rComments: Lots of information for a half year course. I wanted to learn more about my surroundings, but instead ended up feeling helpless and confused.

The course was pretty heavy material and having to stuff that into two hourlong lectures a week was quite a struggle but she really took advice to heart and was constantly looking for feedback which was a good sign. The textbook wasn't essential but made understanding the content a whole lot easier

Prof. Finkelstein is super approachable and understanding. She's very knowledgable and passionate about Earth sciences, which is very visible in her lectures. She combines the textbook readings and new information in lectures very effectively so you're learning from both!

Finkelstein is an amazing Prof. She is so knowledgeable and I could listen to her lecture all day. She is super passionate in what she does and you can tell she wants to share her knowledge with her students. She is super understanding and the midterms and exams are pretty easy. The labs were enjoyable too. I highly recommend this course and prof

The biggest problem of this class is the amount of material. The point of a facilitator is to convey the information in a way that is memorable by using examples that somehow shed light on the topic and emphasize important aspects. Professor Finkelstein, in my view, overestimates the avarage speed of processing so much in such little time.

Dr. Finkelstein is an amazing prof who truly cares about her students. She is very kind and her lectures are very well done. She even boosted everyone's midterm marks up because she felt bad that we had too little time to write it. She truly wants you to succeed. However, the course does have heavy textbook use.
She is a very good prof. PPT was very clear to understand and well-organized. Tests were not hard unless you memorize the slides.

One of the best profs I've had! She is extremely smart, professional, organised, and caring. Also she encourages students to get help, which is always available. I talked to her once at the start of the term and she remembered my name throughout the term, which is super comforting--especially when it's so easy to feel like a # in a place like UofT.
Great class, but took a lot more effort than I thought. If you put in the time, its pretty easy to get a B+ or higher

I'm not a math/science person and I took this class for breadth requirement, but I couldn't recommend it more! She was such an interesting and concise speaker, I was riveted every lecture. I found the labs and tests to be challenging, but she and her TAs always made themselves available and were very helpful.

She's a good prof, nice, caring, organized, pretty. There's an equal use of textbook and lectures. Do the assignments in groups, answer them together but WRITE them yourself.It can be frustrating  doing it alone. Start early, the assignments aren't so bad. Simple math. Ask for help,really, if only I realized earlier not near the end of the semester
Definitely go for office hours, study hard and make good use of the text book :)
Very organized and clear. Lectures summarize and explain hard concepts from readings. Very visual; uses a lot of videos/pictures on slides. Very helpful.
extremely well-organized and enthusiastic teacher.  lots of work, but it's rivotting stuff.  Sarah's very kind and keen on maximizing the student experience.  prepare to learn!
Good lectures, clear, approachable, and easy on the eyes?! Wicked prof! Just do your work, and your good.
Amazing prof. and very helpful and understanding! :)

Very visual. Lecture slides are lots of pictures so you have to attend to attend class toknow what is important.  I didn't know what to expect but was the best class of the year! Approachable and easy marker, but you have to know HOW to apply material.
